Erdogan Facebook Critic May Get Two Years in Jail, Star Says

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-10-18T10:15:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/erdogan-facebook-critic-may-get-two-years-in-jail-star-says.html
Turkish prosecutors want a person
jailed for two years on charges of insulting Prime Minister
 Recep Tayyip Erdogan  on Facebook Inc., the world’s largest
social network, Star newspaper said.  The chief prosecutor’s office in Ankara is leading an
investigation into the allegations, Star  reported , citing a
legal complaint. Prosecutor Adem Can started preparing charges
against the suspect after an e-mailed tip to the prime
minister’s communications office, the newspaper said.  Police raided the defendant’s home and reviewed computer
files seized during the operation, Star reported. Prosecutors
are suing the person for insulting Erdogan, Parliament Speaker
Cemil Cicek, ministers and lawmakers verbally, in writing and
with images and videos, the complaint says, according to the
newspaper.  The defendant said in a testimony that the acts were based
on friends’ incitations and weren’t intended to be malicious,
Star reported. The person expressed regret and said insulting
Erdogan and his ministers, as well as rude phrases during chats
with friends, weren’t intended for public disclosure, according
to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  